				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Hi everyone! First post here on the boards.
<br />

<br />
I am new to the Necro class but have been playing EQ for over 4 years. My main on Drinal is a 44 Beastlord, Nanndas. So I'm also used to playing with a pet. 
<br />

<br />
I need some general guidlines to follow.
<br />

<br />
Atm Nanndar is level 4. Would have made 6 if I didn't spend so much time lost in Neriak..  <img src="images/smiles/icon_evil.gif" alt="Evil or Very Mad" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
He has 307 hp's, 202 mana, 99AC and 153 int. This is only with 1 ear, chest, back, hands, 2 x 6-65 rings, range, legs and boots as well as misty picnics and Qeynos tea (Nanndas is a GM baker). I will be gradually filling the other slots but would like to know what to concentrate on, Int or hp/ac? I like to melee but if I pull with a DoT and send my pet in the mob dies rather quickly. I don't get hit that much, therefore my defence doesn't go up very often. I bought a 10/22 1hb and a 9/21 1hp weapon. Even those skills go up so slowly. 
<br />

<br />
I understand that Necro's power is in spells so when would we stop meleeing? 
<br />

<br />
Do we use shields?
<br />

<br />
Can our pet use Mage toys like the mask, hands ?
<br />

<br />
I tried to buff my pet with minor shielding but it didn't take. Can the pets be buffed and how do we or can we heal them?
<br />

<br />
What spell skills do I need to work on more? Some are not used often and I suspect I'll pay the price later on. What should he specialize in?
<br />

<br />
Thanks in advance
<br />

<br />
Nan  <img src="images/smiles/icon_biggrin.gif" alt="Very Happy" border="0" /><br />_________________<br />Nanndar
<br />
Level 14 Necro, Drinal
