				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Nanndar wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">I will be gradually filling the other slots but would like to know what to concentrate on, Int or hp/ac?</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
Int until you reach 200, then importance is roughly
<br />
Focuses &gt; Mana Regen &gt; HPs &gt; HPs regen &gt; mana &gt; int
<br />
HPs regen falls under mana when you reach lvl 49 (and start getting efficient lifetaps over time), HPs lower to mana's importance once you break the 3khps limit
<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">I like to melee but if I pull with a DoT and send my pet in the mob dies rather quickly. I don't get hit that much, therefore my defence doesn't go up very often. I bought a 10/22 1hb and a 9/21 1hp weapon. Even those skills go up so slowly. 
<br />

<br />
I understand that Necro's power is in spells so when would we stop meleeing? </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
15th-20ish levels i'd say, you can still whack mobs while fear kitting if you feel like it though
<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Do we use shields?</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
Well necromancers can use shields (since we can't dual wield), but they're not a defense feature or anything, just regular items
<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Can our pet use Mage toys like the mask, hands ?</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
Yes, pet has to be lvl 40 (not you, your pet) to proc some of the mages weapons
<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">I tried to buff my pet with minor shielding but it didn't take. Can the pets be buffed and how do we or can we heal them?</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
Minor Shielding is a self only spell (yellow icon), the pet spells we have are mainly hastes and a few heals, and at lvl 16 a little AC buff (same as cleric's)
<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">What spell skills do I need to work on more? Some are not used often and I suspect I'll pay the price later on. What should he specialize in?</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
You need to work on every single spell skill, most importants being (in that order) Alteration (lifetaps, DoTs, ...), Conjuration (some DoTs [snares], pets summonings) and Abjuration (self shields and FD).
<br />
Specialization (lvl 20) should be Alteration (but remember that you have to put a starting point in every single spec)<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=11243" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://masklinnscans.free.fr/pninja.jpg" border="0" /></a>
<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>balidet RZ/AD wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">do you really feel the need to stack [...] dots on boss mobs?</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
Balidet, you win EQ</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
